data.chText: 证据；证明
data.enText: information, documents, etc. that show that sth is true

data.chText: 确切的 / 确凿的证据
data.enText: positive/conclusive proof

data.chText: 你能提供什么身份证明吗？
data.enText: Can you provide any proof of identity ?

data.chText: 保存收据，作为购物证明。
data.enText: Keep the receipt as proof of purchase .

data.chText: 没有证据证明那把刀子是属于她的。
data.enText: There is no proof that the knife belonged to her.

data.chText: 这些成果进一步证明了他的杰出才干。
data.enText: These results are a further proof of his outstanding ability.

data.chText: 检验；证实
data.enText: the process of testing whether sth is true or a fact

data.chText: 这个说法能证明是正确的吗？
data.enText: Is the claim capable of proof?

data.chText: 证明；求证；验算
data.enText: a way of proving that a statement is true or that what you have calculated is correct

data.chText: 校样
data.enText: a copy of printed material which is produced so that mistakes can be corrected

data.chText: 她正在审阅她的新小说的校样。
data.enText: She was checking the proofs of her latest novel.

data.chText: （酒的）标准酒精度
data.enText: a standard used to measure the strength of alcoholic drinks
the proof of the pudding (is in the eating)

data.chText: 只有通过体验才能判断事物的好坏
data.enText: you can only judge if sth is good or bad when you have tried it
be living proof of sth/that…

data.chText: （用行动或品格）证明…属实
data.enText: to show by your actions or qualities that a particular fact is true

data.chText: 并非所有工程师都缺乏情趣，他就是活生生的例子。
data.enText: He is living proof that not all engineers are boring.

data.chText: 能抵御；能防范；可防护
data.enText: that can resist the damaging or harmful effects of sth

data.chText: 防波堤挡不住海浪的力量。
data.enText: The sea wall was not proof against the strength of the waves.

data.chText: 防…的；抗…的
data.enText: that can resist or protect against the thing mentioned

data.chText: 防雨 / 防风服装
data.enText: rainproof/windproof clothing

data.chText: 汽车后门装有防止儿童开启的锁。
data.enText: The car has childproof locks on the rear doors.

data.chText: 已考虑通货膨胀的养老金计划
data.enText: an inflation-proof pension plan

data.chText: 给（织物等）做防护处理；使防水（或防火等）
data.enText: to put a special substance on sth, especially cloth, to protect it against water, fire, etc.

data.chText: 做过防水处理的帆布
data.enText: proofed canvas

data.chText: 印…的校样
data.enText: to produce a test copy of a piece of printed work so that mistakes can be corrected

data.chText: 印彩色校样
data.enText: colour proofing

ex.chText: 最近的这次晋升进一步证明了吉姆的工作干得有多出色。
ex.enText: The latest promotion was further proof of how good at his job Jim was.

ex.chText: 没有证据证明这个男人偷了你的钱包。
ex.enText: There is no proof that this man stole your purse.

synonyms.bx: 指可以表明某事物真实性的信息、文件等。

ex.chText: 我们有表明火星上存在生命的证据吗？
ex.enText: Do we have evidence of life on Mars?

ex.chText: 有证据表明他的新教学法很管用。
ex.enText: There is evidence that his new teaching method works.

ex.chText: 这些信件可以在庭审时用作证据。
ex.enText: These letters may be used as evidence at the trial.

synonyms.bx: 指表明某事物存在或真实的事实、迹象等，也指法庭上证明某人有罪或无罪的证据。

ex.chText: 这些成就是你勤奋努力的证明。
ex.enText: These achievements are a testimony to your diligence.

ex.chText: 那名小贩的证词对控方的起诉起着关键作用。
ex.enText: That vendor's testimony is crucial to the prosecution's case.

synonyms.bx: 指清楚表明某事物存在或属实的事实或情况，也指法庭上的证词。

ex.enText: The defense has to find the key witness.
The prosecution witness didn't appear in court.

ex.chText: 那座纪念碑屹立在那里，作为对这一事件的见证。
ex.enText: The monument stands there in witness of the event.

synonyms.bx: 多指知道案件情况并在法庭上对其进行陈述的人，也可指证据或证言。

tr: finding or testing the truth of something
a trial photographic print from a negative
any factual evidence that helps to establish the truth of something
example: if you have any proof for what you say, now is the time to produce it

tr: (printing) an impression made to check for errors
a formal series of statements showing that if one thing is true something else necessarily follows from it
a measure of alcoholic strength expressed as an integer twice the percentage of alcohol present (by volume)

example: proof the materials against shrinking in the dryer

tr: activate by mixing with water and sometimes sugar or milk
make or take a proof of, such as a photographic negative, an etching, or typeset

value.def: Proof is a fact, argument, or piece of evidence which shows that something is definitely true or definitely exists.

example.ex: You have to have proof of residence in the state of Texas, such as a Texas ID card...
example.tran: 你必须有在得克萨斯州的居住证明，比如得克萨斯身份证。

example.ex: This is not necessarily proof that he is wrong...
example.tran: 这不一定就证明他是错的。

example.ex: Economists have been concerned with establishing proofs for their arguments.
example.tran: 经济学家一直致力于为他们的观点寻找证据。

value.def: In publishing, the proofs of a book, magazine, or article are a first copy of it that is printed so that mistakes can be corrected before more copies are printed and published.

example.ex: I'm correcting the proofs of the Spanish edition right now.
example.tran: 我正在校正西班牙语版本的校样。

example.ex: ...an uncorrected proof copy of the book.

value.def: Proof is used after a number of degrees or a percentage, when indicating the strength of a strong alcoholic drink such as whisky.

example.ex: ...a glass of Wild Turkey bourbon: 101 degrees proof.
example.tran: 一杯威特基波旁威士忌：酒精度为101°

value.def: If something or someone is proof against a particular thing, they cannot be damaged, harmed, or affected by it.

example.ex: The fortress was proof against the techniques of attack then in use...
example.tran: 该防御工事能抵御当时所使用的各种进攻手段。

example.ex: His papers were proof against all but the most expert of scrutinies.
example.tran: 他的论文几乎可以经受住最专业的审查。

value.tran: 不能穿透的；耐…的；能防…的

value.def: If you say that someone is living proof of something, you mean that their actions or personal qualities show that a particular fact is true or that a particular quality exists.

example.ex: He is living proof that some players just get better with age.
example.tran: 有些运动员年纪越大状态越好，他就是个活生生的例子。

gramarinfo.label: usu v-link PHR, oft PHR that, PHR <l>of</l> n

value.tran: 典型的例证；活生生的例子

value.def: To be proof positive of a particular fact or quality means to be evidence that it is true or that it exists.

example.ex: The Windermere Golf Club is proof positive that golf and ecology can co-exist in perfect harmony.
example.tran: 温德米尔高尔夫俱乐部证明了高尔夫和生态能完全和谐共存。
